    <gsw_content_information action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <article><![CDATA[<p>Set the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.mid_server</em> system property to the <strong>name</strong> of the MID server which should be able to access your Tanium &#34;on-prem&#34; server, and then mark this step as Complete. <br />This property should be set to a MID server name, not sys_id. For example: &#34;<em>my-mid-server</em>&#34;. You can find your list of MID servers in the <strong><a title="ecc_agent" href="nav_to.do?uri&#61;%2Fecc_agent_list.do" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">ecc_agent</a></strong> table.</p>
<p>If you&#39;re using Tanium Cloud / Tanium as a Service (TaaS), you may <strong>skip this step</strong>. </p>]]></article>
